(the native form of this personal name is nagy lászló. this article uses the western name order.) lászló nagy (born 3 march 1981) is a hungarian international handball player who plays for and captains mvm veszprém kc. among his achievements at club level are several spanish championships and cup titles and he also won the ehf champions league, the top continental competition in europe two times (2005, 2011). with the hungarian national team, nagy's best results are two fourth places from the 2004 summer olympics and 2012 summer olympics nagy was voted by the readers of the handball journal handball planet as the world's best male player in 2011.